        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry and blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the butter into the flour and salt until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add the water and bring together. Wrap and rest for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 190°C conventional. Roll to 3 mm thick and line a 23 cm loose-bottomed fluted tart tin. Line with baking paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 20 minutes. Remove beans and paper, brush the base with a little beaten egg (from the filling), and bake for a further 8 minutes until dry and pale gold.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sweat the leeks",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the butter in a wide pan over low heat. Add the leeks and salt, stir to coat, and cover with a lid. Cook for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until completely soft and sweet but not coloured. Remove the lid for the last 5 minutes to drive off any excess moisture. Spread on a plate to cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Reduce the oven to 180°C conventional. Scatter half the Gruyère over the base of the pastry case. Spread the cooled leeks evenly over the cheese. Whisk the eggs, cream, pepper, and nutmeg together and pour over the leeks. Scatter the remaining Gruyère on top. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the custard is just set with the slightest quiver in the centre. Allow to cool in the tin for 10 minutes before removing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
